Core Enforcer 10 100 100 If the target has already used their moves, this move cancels the effect of its abilities.

Dragon Claw 15 80 100 The user slashes the target with huge sharp claws.
Dragon Dance 20 — — The user vigorously performs a mystic dance that raises its Attack and Speed stats.
Dragon Darts 10 50 100 The user attacks twice using Dreepy. In case of two targets, each is hit once.
Dragon Energy 5 150 100 The user hits opposing Pokémon with its life-force. The move's power scales with the user's HP.
Dragon Hammer 15 90 100 The user uses its body like a hammer to attack the target and inflict damage.
Dragon Pulse 10 85 100 The target is attacked with a shock wave generated by the user's gaping mouth.
Dragon Rage 10 — 100 The target is hit by a shock wave of pure rage. This attack always inflicts 40 HP damage.
Dragon Rush 10 100 75 The user tackles the target with overwhelming menace. This may also make it flinch.
Dragon Tail 10 60 90 The target is knocked away and switched. This ends a battle against a single wild Pokémon.

Fickle Beam 5 80 100 Shoots a beam of light to inflict damage, sometimes doubling in power.
Glaive Rush 5 120 100 A reckless charge causes attacks from enemies to be powered up and not miss.
Order Up 10 80 100 The user attacks with elegant poise.
Outrage 10 120 100 The user rampages and attacks for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.
Predation 10 60 100 The user feasts on the target's flesh, restoring its HP by half the damage caused.
Primal Terrain 10 — — For 5 turns, STAB is ignored and Dragon type-moves are stronger.
Roar of Time 5 150 90 The user blasts the target with power that distorts even time but can't move on the next turn.
Scale Shot 20 25 90 The user shoots scales two to five times. This ups its Speed but lowers its Defense stat.
Spacial Rend 5 100 95 The user tears the target along with the space around it. Critical hits land more easily.
Twister 20 40 100 A vicious twister is whipped up to tear at opposing Pokémon. It may also make them flinch.
